  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-df477e80-7fff-c891-faca-47aa2f7134c0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed mansard roof extension, by reason of its size, bulk, massing, and detailed design, is considered to be an inappropriate, obtrusive, and unsympathetic addition to the property and the terrace that it forms part of. The detailed design of the mansard fails to comply with the guidance in the SPD, and the mansard itself would be located within a terrace with an unbroken roof line and a strong parapet that would be lost. The proposal is, therefore, contrary to London Plan (2021) policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and D4 (Delivering good design) and Hackney Local Plan (2020) policy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character)&amp;nbsp; and the advice set out in Hackney&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
